This topic provides instructions for installing the NSX Manager VM on vSphere for use with <%= vars.product_full %>.

##<a id='prereqs'></a> Prerequisites

Complete the [Prerequisites for Installing NSX-T for <%= vars.product_short %>](./nsxt-install-prereqs.html).

##<a id='nsx-mgr-about'></a> About the NSX Manager Appliance

The NSX-T Manager VM is provided as an OVA file named the **NSX Unified Appliance** that you import into your vSphere environment and configure. 

For more information, see [Install the NSX Manager Unified Appliance](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-NSX-T-Data-Center/2.5/installation/GUID-FA0ABBBD-34D8-4DA9-882D-085E7E0D269E.html) in the NSX-T Data Center documentation. See also [NSX Manager VM System Requirements](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-NSX-T-Data-Center/2.5/installation/GUID-AECA2EE0-90FC-48C4-8EDB-66517ACFE415.html).

##<a id='nsx-mgr-install'></a> Install and Configure the NSX Manager Appliance

Complete the following procedure to deploy the NSX Manager appliance:

1. Locate the NSX-T Data Center OVA file, `nsx-unified-appliance-VERSION.ova`, on the VMware download portal and download it to your local machine.

1. Log in to vCenter using the vSphere Client.

1. Create a **Resource Pool** for NSX-T infrastructure, such as `infra`.

1. In the vSphere Client, select the **Resource Pool** where you want to install NSX-T Data Center.

1. Right-click and select **Deploy OVF Template** to start the installation wizard.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-00.png">

1. On the **Select an OVF template** screen:
  1. Select the **Local file** option.
  1. Click **Choose Files**.
  1. Navigate to where you downloaded the OVA file and select it.
  1. Click **Next**.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-01.png">

1. On the **Select a name and folder** screen:
  1. Enter a name for the NSX Manager VM, such as `nsx-manager-1`.
  1. Select the **Datacenter** for the VM deployment.
  1. Click **Next**.  
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-02.png">

1. On the **Select a compute resource** screen:
  1. Select the **Resource Pool** where the NSX Manager VM will be deployed.
  1. Click **Next**.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-03.png">

1. On the **Review details** screen:
  1. Verify the OVF template details.
  1. Click **Next**.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-04.png">

1. On the **Configuration** screen:
  1. Select either the **Medium** size VM or the **Large** size VM.
  1. Click **Next**.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-05.png">

1. On the **Select storage** screen:
  1. Select the **vsanDatastore** if you are using vSAN, or a dedicated datastore if you are not.
  1. Click **Next**.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-06.png">

1. On the **Select networks** screen:
  1. Select **Destination Network** for the NSX Manager VM.
  1. Click **Next**. 
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-07.png">

1. On the **Customize Template** screen, configure the following settings:
  - **System Root User Password**: This password must comply with password strength restrictions.
  - **CLI "admin" User Password**: This password must comply with password strength restrictions.
  - **CLI "audit" User Password**: This password must comply with password strength restrictions.
  - **Hostname**: Enter the hostname for the NSX Manager VM, such as `nsx-manager-1`.
  - **Default IPv4 Gateway**: Enter the default gateway IPv4 address for the NSX Manager VM.
  - **Management Network IPv4 Address**: Enter the IPv4 address for the first network interface.
  - **Management Network Netmask**: Enter the netmask for the first network interface.
  - **DNS Server List**: Enter one or more DNS servers (space-separated if multiple).
  - **NTP Server List**: Enter one or more NTP servers (space-separated if multiple).
  - **Enable SSH**: Select **Enable SSH**. By default, this setting is disabled for security reasons.
  - **Allow root SSH logins**: Enable **Allow root SSH logins**. By default, this setting is disabled for security reasons.
  - Click **Next**    
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-08.png">
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-09.png">
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-10.png">
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-11.png">

1. On the **Ready to complete** screen:
  1. Verify that the OVF template specification is accurate.
  1. Click **Finish** to begin the installation. It takes approximately 10 minutes to complete.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-manager-installation/nsx-manager-install-13.png">

1. Expand the **Recent Tasks** panel at the bottom of the vCenter screen to view the progress of the OVA deployment.

##<a id='nsx-mgr-verify'></a> Verify NSX-T Manager Installation

1. From your browser, log in with admin privileges to the NSX Manager user interface at `https://NSX-MANAGER-IP-ADDRESS`.

1. If you are logging in to the NSX Manager user interface for the first time, read and accept the EULA terms.

1. Select whether to join the VMware's Customer Experience Improvement Program (CEIP) and click **Save**.

1. Navigate to the **Advanced Networking & Security** tab. This is the tab to use for creating and working with NSX-T objects for <%= vars.product_short %>.
  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-24-ui.png" alt="NSX-T v2.4 User Interface" width="725">

  <p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> <%= vars.product_short %> does not support the <code>Simplified UI/API</code>. For <%= vars.product_short %>, you must use the <code>Advanced Networking and Security</code> tab to create, read, update, and delete required network objects. For NSX-T host preparation and configuration, such as deploying NSX-T Managers and Edge Nodes, use the <code>System</code> tab.</p>

